## Integration Guardrails

### Signal Integration Guardrails
- ‚úÖ **DO**: Use 1-on-1 PMs for all vetting operations
- ‚úÖ **DO**: Verify Freenet state before Signal actions
- ‚úÖ **DO**: Execute immediate ejection when threshold violated
- ‚ùå **DON'T**: Store Signal IDs in any form
- ‚ùå **DON'T**: Expose operations in group chat
- ‚ùå **DON'T**: Make Signal group the source of truth

### Freenet Integration Guardrails
- ‚úÖ **DO**: Use ComposableState trait for all contract state
- ‚úÖ **DO**: Use set-based structures (BTreeSet, HashMap) for mergeability
- ‚úÖ **DO**: Generate Merkle Trees on-demand (not stored in contract)
- ‚úÖ **DO**: Implement summary-delta synchronization
- ‚úÖ **DO**: Test merge semantics are commutative (order-independent)
- ‚úÖ **DO**: Use tombstones for deletions (grow-only sets)
- ‚ùå **DON'T**: Store Merkle Trees as primary state (not mergeable)
- ‚ùå **DON'T**: Use Vec for state (order matters, not easily mergeable)
- ‚ùå **DON'T**: Bypass ComposableState trait (required by freenet-scaffold)
- ‚ùå **DON'T**: Expose member identities in contract state (use hashes)

### Cryptographic Guardrails
- ‚úÖ **DO**: Use `ring` for all HMAC operations
- ‚úÖ **DO**: Zeroize all sensitive buffers immediately
- ‚úÖ **DO**: Use deterministic hashing for tests
- ‚ùå **DON'T**: Use non-audited cryptographic libraries
- ‚ùå **DON'T**: Skip zeroization of keys or identifiers
- ‚ùå **DON'T**: Use pre-shared keys for federation

